olive oil
1 packet peeled pumpkin pieces
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 pear
1 bag Mixed Leaves
1 drizzle balsamic vinegar
1 packet filo pastry
¼ packet Greek salad cheese/feta cheese
1 tbs milk
1 packet Chargrilled Capsicum Relish
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan forced. On a lined oven tray place peeled
pumpkin pieces, then sprinkle with garlic & herb seasoning.
• Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat. Roast until tender,
15-20 minutes.

• While pumpkin is roasting, thinly slice pear.
• In a medium bowl, add mixed leaves, pear, a drizzle of balsamic vinegar
and olive oil. Season to taste and set aside.

TIP: Toss the salad just before serving to keep the leaves crisp.

• When pumpkin is done, remove from tray and transfer to a plate.
• Place filo pastry flat on the lined oven tray. Place roasted pumpkin in
centre of the pastry, leaving a 4cm border around edge.
• Sprinkle over shredded Cheddar cheese and crumble over Greek salad
cheese (see ingredients).
• Carefully fold pastry edges over pumpkin, leaving the centre exposed.
Brush edges of pastry with milk. Bake in the oven until golden,
15-20 minutes.

TIP: Use the same lined oven tray from the pumpkin to cook your pastry,
for extra flavour!

• Toss salad and slice galette. Divide pumpkin and Cheddar filo galette
between plates.
• Dollop with chargrilled capsicum relish. Serve with pear salad. Enjoy!